## 2. Critical Priorities (Vulnerability Patching & Hardening)
*Goal: Address known Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerabilities and critical misconfigurations within 24–48 hours.*

| Priority | Action Item | Specific Steps | Resources/Tools | Effort | Impact |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- :--- | :--- |
| **P0** | **Patch vsftpd Backdoor** | 1. **Do not** simply update the package if the binary is compromised.<br>2. Reinstall vsftpd from a trusted source or replace the binary entirely.<br>3. Verify the binary hash against the vendor's official release.<br>4. Upgrade to the latest stable version (CVE-2011-2523 mitigation). | Vendor Repos, Hash Verification | 2 hrs | **Critical** |
| **P0** | **Patch Samba (EternalBlue Risk)** | 1. Upgrade Samba from 3.0.20 to the latest stable version (4.x+).<br>2. Disable SMBv1 protocol entirely (`min protocol = SMB2` in `smb.conf`).<br>3. Enable SMB Signing (`ntlm auth = yes`, `server signing = mandatory`).<br>4. Address CVE-2017-7494 (EternalBlue) and CVE-2007-2447. | `apt/yum update`, `smb.conf` | 4 hrs | **Critical** |
